      <title>Professional Development Week </title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52737592201257/huge/a5dee205ef28b009712153be617949c39e5412a1.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Mon, 18 May 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Please save the date for Howard University’s inaugural Professional Development Week, taking place virtually from May 18–22, 2026. </p>

<p>This university-wide week of learning and connection unites employees around shared growth, reflection, and professional development. Themed “The Bison Way,” the week highlights how we lead, serve, collaborate, and grow as a community. </p>

<p>Employees are invited to participate in a variety of sessions designed to strengthen skills, build systems knowledge, and prepare intentionally for the semester ahead. To learn more about The Bison Way framework, we encourage you to visit the Culture Hub. </p>

<p>Registration is now open — sign up below to take part in Professional Development Week.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Professional Development Week at a Glance </p>

<p>Monday, May 18 – Bravery 
<br>Welcome &amp; Introduction: The Bison Way (Welcome to PD Week)
<br>Virtual Keynote: Dr. Dawn Williams, Interim Provost &amp; Chief Academic Officer</p>

<p>Tuesday, May 19 – Service Excellence  
<br>Virtual Panel: From Good to Exceptional: What Service Excellence Really Requires</p>

<p>Wednesday, May 20 – Inclusiveness &amp; Growth 
<br>Learning Hours: Inclusive Habits, Not Intentions</p>

<p>Thursday, May 21 – Ownership 
<br>Self-Led Learning Courses: Owning the Journey, Building a Mindset of Accountability</p>

<p>Friday, May 22 – Novelty &amp; Innovation 
<br>System Skills Development: Microsoft Outlook</p>

